text: Yandenberry is a remote civil parish of Yantara County in far northwest New South Wales. located at 30°19′15″S 142°26′32″E, east of the Silver City Highway. Yantara County The geography of the parish is mostly the flat, arid landscape of the Channel Country. The parish has a Köppen climate classification of BWh (hot desert). (direct: Final Revised Paper) The nearest town is Tibooburra to the north west, which is on the Silver City Highway and lies south of the Sturt National Park. ==References== Category:Parishes of Yantara County Category:Localities in New South Wales Category:Far West (New South Wales)
title: Parish of Yandenberry
